1
00:00:02,436 --> 00:00:06,638
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.    
<i>[ Sydney ] SL-27.</i>               


2
00:00:06,707 --> 00:00:08,339
<i>WHAT DOES IT MEAN, JACOB?</i>       


3
00:00:08,408 --> 00:00:11,810
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>I BELIEVE MY MOTHER RESCUED</i>     
<i>SOME OF THE CHILDREN HERE.</i>      


4
00:00:11,879 --> 00:00:14,145
[ Man ]                         
RESCUED?                        
            IT'S A LONG STORY.  


5
00:00:14,214 --> 00:00:17,749
    - YOU HAVE A PROBLEM        
      WITH RAINES?              
    - HE IS OUT OF CONTROL.     


6
00:00:17,818 --> 00:00:21,853
WHEN YOU WERE DR. RAINES,       
YOU WERE MY COLLEAGUE.          


7
00:00:21,922 --> 00:00:25,957
I NEVER DETECTED                
THIS UNHOLY OBSESSION.          


8
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:28,526
                YOU DIDN'T LOOK 
                HARD ENOUGH.    


9
00:00:29,830 --> 00:00:31,763
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>TONIGHT ON</i> THE PRETENDER.       


10
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:36,701
[ Young Sydney ]                
VERY GOOD WORK, JAROD.          
YOU'RE MAKING PROGRESS.         


11
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:44,542
            <i> [ Young Jarod ]</i>    
            <i> SIDNEY? WHO'S THAT?</i>
            <i> WHO'S THAT BOY?</i>    


12
00:00:44,611 --> 00:00:46,612
<i>ANOTHER TEST SUBJECT.</i>           


13
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:50,582
            HE'S WORKING        
            WITH ANOTHER DOCTOR.


14
00:00:50,651 --> 00:00:53,284
            <i> WHAT'S HIS NAME?</i>   
            <i> CAN I TALK TO HIM?</i> 
<i>NO.</i>                             


15
00:00:53,353 --> 00:00:57,189
                BUT I DON'T HAVE
                ANY FRIENDS.    
YOU WON'T BE SEEING HIM AGAIN.  


16
00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:06,531
<i>SYDNEY, WHERE ARE</i>               
<i>THEY TAKING HIM?</i>                


17
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:09,734
<i>YEAH. THIS IS GARRISON.</i>         
<i>FLIGHT 1701.</i>                    


18
00:01:09,803 --> 00:01:14,173
TELL THE OKLAHOMA OFFICE        
WE HAVE THEIR WITNESS,          
SEALED AND READY TO DELIVER.    


19
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:16,741
    REMIND THEM WE'VE GOT       
    BETTER THINGS TO DO         
    THAN ESCORT THEIR CHAMELEON.


20
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:20,412
GOT THAT? YEAH. 1701 OUT.       


21
00:01:20,481 --> 00:01:22,781
            STILL NO UPDATE     
            ON EUGENE'S LOCALE. 


22
00:01:22,850 --> 00:01:24,782
            THAT'S ALL RIGHT.   
            WE'LL FIND HIM...   


23
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:28,920
JUST AS SOON                    
AS WE FINISH PLAYING ESCORT     
TO THE MAN OF A THOUSAND FACES. 


24
00:01:28,989 --> 00:01:31,622
    COME ON!                    
    LET'S GO IN THERE.          


25
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:41,300
<i>HEY, LON CHANEY,</i>                
<i>HURRY IT UP IN THERE.</i>           


26
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:50,341
        HO! MARSHAL CODY.       


27
00:01:51,745 --> 00:01:53,478
        HOW DO I LOOK?          


28
00:01:56,717 --> 00:02:00,118
    WELL, IT'S A FACE           
    ONLY A MOTHER COULD LOVE.   


29
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:04,589
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


30
00:02:51,772 --> 00:02:53,738
OH, GOD.                        


31
00:02:53,807 --> 00:02:56,240
        UNPUCKER YOUR SPHINCTER,
        BROOTS. IT'S JUST ME.   


32
00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:59,678
MISS PARKER, I DIDN'T--         
[ Clears Throat ]               
HEAR YOU COME IN.               


33
00:02:59,746 --> 00:03:02,214
        AND HOW'S YOUR LITTLE   
        JOHN TESH FAN?          


34
00:03:03,751 --> 00:03:05,784
FINE. SHE'S-SHE'S FINE.         


35
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:09,053
I'LL, UH-- I'LL TELL HER        
YOU SAID HELLO.                 


36
00:03:10,424 --> 00:03:14,058
UM, IS THERE SOMETHING          
ON YOUR MIND?                   


37
00:03:14,128 --> 00:03:16,128
        I NEED A PERSONAL FAVOR.


38
00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:18,296
    FROM ME?                    


39
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:20,698
    IS IT POSSIBLE TO RUN       
    A GLOBAL INTERNET SEARCH... 


40
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,701
        WITHOUT ANYONE          
        FROM THE CENTRE KNOWING?


41
00:03:22,769 --> 00:03:26,238
OH, I GUESS, YES.               
BUT IF THEY--                   


42
00:03:26,306 --> 00:03:29,707
IF THEY, UH, CATCH YOU,         
THEY'D CRUCIFY YOU.             


43
00:03:29,777 --> 00:03:33,244
WHY? YOU WANT ME TO SEE         
IF SOMEONE'S BEEN DOING IT?     


44
00:03:33,313 --> 00:03:35,313
    I WANT YOU TO DO IT FOR ME. 


45
00:03:37,184 --> 00:03:39,885
NO. NO, I COULDN'T DO THAT.     


46
00:03:39,953 --> 00:03:41,753
            PLEASE.             


47
00:03:44,357 --> 00:03:46,358
[ Sighs ]                       


48
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,062
        OKAY.                   


49
00:03:55,168 --> 00:03:58,002
    THESE ARE MISSING CHILDREN  
    FROM THE LATE '60s.         


50
00:04:06,212 --> 00:04:09,147
            NAMES, BIRTHDAYS,   
            PHYSICAL ATTRIBUTES,
            SOME PHOTOS.        


51
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:12,617
            NOBODY CAN SEE THIS.


52
00:04:12,686 --> 00:04:16,588
    DO NOT SCAN THESE PICTURES  
    AND DON'T TRANSMIT THEM     
    OVER THE INTERNET.          


53
00:04:17,891 --> 00:04:21,226
    BUT--                       
        IF YOU FIND ANYTHING,   
        FIND ME.                


54
00:04:41,348 --> 00:04:45,517
WELL, IF IT ISN'T               
THE KEYSTONE KOPS.              
[ Chuckling ]                   


55
00:04:45,585 --> 00:04:49,287
    WE SPEND OUR LIVES          
    KEEPIN' MOB SNITCHES ALIVE, 
    AND ALL WE GET IS GRIEF.    


56
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:52,957
THERE'S A BUNCH OF GUYS         
WITH FLAT NOSES THAT WOULD LIKE 
TO GET THEIR HANDS ON YOU.      


57
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:56,528
WITH MARSHAL CODY HERE--        
NEVER HAPPEN.                   


58
00:04:56,596 --> 00:04:59,898
<i>UNLIKE YOU AND GARRISON,</i>        
<i>HE'S NEVER LOST A WITNESS.</i>      


59
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:02,634
    OH, YEAH? WELL,             
    ALL I KNOW IS THE QUICKER   
    WE DUMP YOUR BUTT,          


60
00:05:02,703 --> 00:05:04,902
        THE SOONER WE CAN       
        GET BACK ON OUR CASE.   


61
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:07,872
    <i> [ Garrison ] COOL IT, LANE.</i>
    <i> MARSHAL CODY'S JUST TRYIN'</i> 
    <i> TO DO HIS JOB.</i>             


62
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:10,575
        LET'S GO IN THE BACK    
        AND GET YOU SOMETHIN'   
        TO DRINK.               


63
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,783
        YOU'RE A FUN GUY.       
[ Laughing ]                    


64
00:05:20,887 --> 00:05:23,922
        DID I MISS SOMETHING?   


65
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,291
ALL THE MARSHALS IN D.C.        
WERE LAUGHIN' ABOUT IT.         


66
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:29,494
HEARD ABOUT IT                  
DURING MY HOLDOVER.             


67
00:05:29,563 --> 00:05:33,431
ONE OF THEIR WITNESSES--        
A GUY NAMED DIGGS--             
HE BOLTS ON THEIR WATCH.        


68
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:37,002
    WELL, IN THIS BUSINESS,     
    THAT SORT OF THING HAPPENS. 


69
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,670
THAT'S ONLY HALF THE STORY.     


70
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:43,341
A COUPLE OF WEEKS BEFORE THAT,  
THIS DIGGS'S PARTNER,           


71
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:46,844
<i>HE CUTS UP GARRISON</i>             
<i>WITH A HOMEMADE KNIFE...</i>        


72
00:05:46,914 --> 00:05:51,582
<i>AND THEN TAKES A DIVE</i>           
<i>FROM 30,000 FEET</i>                
<i>DURING THE PLANE TRANSFER.</i>      


73
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:53,919
    MUST HAVE BEEN              
    PRETTY EMBARRASSING         
    FOR THE MARSHALS SERVICE.   


74
00:05:53,987 --> 00:05:57,555
NOW YOU'RE CATCHING ON.         
I THOUGHT YOU MUST HAVE         
HEARD ABOUT IT.                 


75
00:05:57,624 --> 00:06:00,459
            I'VE BEEN BUSY.     


76
00:06:14,841 --> 00:06:17,108
            [ Tones Beeping ]   


77
00:06:19,579 --> 00:06:22,113
        [ Line Clicks ]         
                    DR. SHAFTON?


78
00:06:22,182 --> 00:06:26,885
            SYDNEY.             
            [ Sniffs ]          
            I NEED TO SEE YOU.  


79
00:06:26,954 --> 00:06:28,886
    LANE.                       


80
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:32,958
LOOK, I KNOW IT MUST FEEL       
LIKE A SLAP IN THE FACE--       


81
00:06:33,026 --> 00:06:35,961
THE SERVICE TRANSFERRING ME     
INTO THE MIDDLE OF YOUR CASE    
LIKE THAT.                      


82
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:41,198
        NOTHING PERSONAL,       
        BUT WE WERE DOIN'       
        JUST FINE WITHOUT YOU.  


83
00:06:41,267 --> 00:06:45,036
        LOOK, THIS DIGGS THING  
        JUST HAS ME ON EDGE.    
        THAT'S ALL.             


84
00:06:45,104 --> 00:06:47,872
I'M HERE TO HELP.               
MIND IF I TAKE A LOOK?          


85
00:06:49,710 --> 00:06:53,511
<i>IN THREE DAYS, EUGENE DIGGS</i>     
<i>IS SUPPOSED TO TESTIFY</i>          
<i>AGAINST THE ARELLANO CARTEL.</i>    


86
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:57,015
<i>IF WE DON'T GET HIM BACK, THE</i>   
<i>GOVERNMENT'S CASE GOES SOUTH</i>    
<i>AND THESE DRUG RUNNERS WALK.</i>    


87
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:59,851
WE'LL GET 'IM BACK.             


88
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:02,387
WE'RE NOT GONNA BREAK FOR CHOW  
TILL WE DO.                     


89
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:12,964
"S-P-A-M."                      
WHAT'S IT STAND FOR?            


90
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,466
                AMERICA.        


91
00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:18,937
        IF WE HADN'T SHIPPED    
        THAT STUFF TO ENGLAND   
        DURING WORLD WAR II,    


92
00:07:19,006 --> 00:07:21,272
        THE BEATLES WOULD'VE    
        SUNG IN GERMAN.         


93
00:07:21,341 --> 00:07:24,642
I IMAGINE THE SOUND OF AN INSECT
VOCALIZING IN ANY LANGUAGE      
WOULD BE FANTASTIC.             


94
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:27,478
DO YOU MIND?                    


95
00:07:31,384 --> 00:07:33,517
MMM. IT'S DELICIOUS.            


96
00:07:33,586 --> 00:07:36,520
<i>[ Lane ]</i>                        
<i>ARE WE GONNA GO TALK</i>            
<i>TO EUGENE'S WIFE OR NOT?</i>        


97
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:44,429
            BEATS HIMSELF UP    
            OVER EVERYTHING.    


98
00:07:44,498 --> 00:07:47,866
            THAT'S ONE BAD HABIT
            I CAN'T GET THAT KID
            TO SHAKE.           


99
00:07:47,935 --> 00:07:49,935
                    <i> COME ON.</i>   


100
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:58,276
DIGGS AND HIS BEST FRIEND,      
JIMMY RAYFORD, OWNED A LITTLE   
AIR CARGO COMPANY IN ARKANSAS.  


101
00:07:58,345 --> 00:08:03,080
        BUSINESS WAS IN TROUBLE,
        SO JIMMY MAKES A DEAL   
        WITH THE COLOMBIANS...  


102
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:05,683
    TO FLY SOME SPECIAL CARGO.  


103
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:08,052
        NOW, EUGENE, WHO TRUSTS 
        JIMMY WITH HIS LIFE,    


104
00:08:08,121 --> 00:08:10,422
        THINKS THEY'RE HAULIN'  
        COFFEE BEANS.           


105
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,657
            OF COURSE, JIMMY'S  
            RUNNIN' COCAINE.    


106
00:08:12,726 --> 00:08:16,861
        D.E.A. NAILS 'EM, SO    
        WE GOT THEM TO TESTIFY  
        AGAINST THE CARTEL...   


107
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:19,464
        FOR REDUCED SENTENCES-- 
        CASE CLOSED.            


108
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:23,635
TILL JIMMY RAYFORD TRIES TO     
ATTACK YOU WITH A HOMEMADE KNIFE
DURING AN AIR TRANSFER,         


109
00:08:23,704 --> 00:08:26,738
TRIES TO ESCAPE                 
BY PARACHUTING OUT              
OF ONE OF OUR PLANES...         


110
00:08:26,806 --> 00:08:29,807
AND LEAVES EUGENE DIGGS         
TO TAKE THE FALL.               


111
00:08:29,876 --> 00:08:33,177
            BAD NEWS            
            TRAVELS FAST, HUH?  


112
00:08:33,247 --> 00:08:35,647
WELL, I GUESS                   
THE BOYS IN WASHINGTON          
AREN'T TOO HAPPY WITH YOU GUYS. 


113
00:08:35,716 --> 00:08:38,583
    [ Laughing ]                
    THEY'RE NOT THE ONLY ONES.  


114
00:08:39,619 --> 00:08:41,753
            HOW THE HELL COULD I
            TALK TO EUGENE?     


115
00:08:41,822 --> 00:08:43,955
    YOU GOT YOUR PEOPLE         
    CAMPED OUT IN MY FRONT YARD.


116
00:08:44,024 --> 00:08:45,957
        YOU GOT MY PHONE LINES  
        TAPPED.                 


117
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:48,460
        MY FRIENDS WON'T EVEN   
        COME NEAR THIS PLACE    
        ANYMORE.                


118
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:50,495
THE TRUTH IS WE MIGHT BE        
THE ONLY FRIENDS                
THAT YOU HAVE LEFT.             


119
00:08:50,564 --> 00:08:53,531
NOW YOU'RE NOT DOIN'            
EUGENE ANY FAVORS               
BY LYIN' TO US.                 


120
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:55,833
            EUGENE IS SCARED.   


121
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:59,270
JIMMY SAID THESE CARTEL GUYS    
WERE TOUGH, THAT THEY'D JUST    
AS SOON KILL YOU AS LOOK AT YOU.


122
00:08:59,339 --> 00:09:01,305
THEN LET US HELP YOU.           


123
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:03,408
                LIKE YOU HELPED 
                JIMMY RAYFORD?  


124
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:15,386
MRS. DIGGS,                     
WE CAN PROTECT YOU,             


125
00:09:16,456 --> 00:09:20,091
<i>BOTH OF YOU,</i>                    
<i>FROM THE CARTEL.</i>                


126
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:23,895
        <i> I TOLD YOU ALREADY.</i>    
         <i> I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.</i>


127
00:09:23,964 --> 00:09:27,999
    <i> HE'S OUT THERE ALONE,</i>      
    <i> SCARED, WITHOUT A FRIEND.</i>  


128
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,334
        WHO CAN HE TRUST NOW?   


129
00:10:01,368 --> 00:10:05,169
JAROD, YOU NEED TO FINISH       
THE SIMULATION.                 


130
00:10:05,238 --> 00:10:07,305
                I WANNA SEE     
                THE OTHER BOY.  


131
00:10:07,374 --> 00:10:09,640
YOU KNOW I CAN'T ALLOW YOU      
TO HAVE CONTACT WITH ANYONE.    


132
00:10:09,709 --> 00:10:13,244
    - FINE. THEN I CAN'T FINISH 
      THE SIMULATION.           
    - WHY NOT?                  


133
00:10:13,313 --> 00:10:15,846
    HOW AM I SUPPOSED           
    TO PRETEND TO DO THIS       
    IF I'VE NEVER HAD A FRIEND? 


134
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:18,883
YOU SIMULATE A LOT OF THINGS    
YOU'VE NEVER DONE BEFORE.       


135
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:22,720
        I WANT TO SEE           
        THE OTHER BOY, SYDNEY.  


136
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:25,723
        I WANT TO KNOW          
        WHAT IT'S LIKE          
        TO HAVE A FRIEND.       


137
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:28,293
                    [ Ringing ] 


138
00:10:31,598 --> 00:10:34,365
            YES?                
            YEAH. IT'S GARRISON.


139
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:37,669
    DIGGS'S LAWYER JUST CAME IN.
    EUGENE WANTS TO TALK.       


140
00:10:37,737 --> 00:10:40,004
        I'M ON MY WAY.          


141
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:49,013
        I HOPE, FOR YOUR SAKE,  
        YOUR CLIENT'S CALLIN'   
        TO GIVE UP.             


142
00:10:49,082 --> 00:10:52,049
I PUT YOU IN CONTACT WITH HIM.  
WHAT, I HAVE TO TALK HIM        
OFF THE LEDGE TOO?              


143
00:10:52,118 --> 00:10:54,051
    [ Groans ]                  
                        SORRY.  


144
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,454
                I FORGOT ABOUT  
                YOUR<i> WAR</i> WOUND. 


145
00:10:56,523 --> 00:10:59,190
DEPUTY MARSHAL JAROD CODY.      
                        CODY.   


146
00:10:59,259 --> 00:11:02,761
            [ Laughs ]          
            GUESS THAT MAKES ME 
            ANNIE OAKLEY.       


147
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:04,929
                    <i> HERE WE GO.</i>
            <i> [ Switch Clicks ]</i>  


148
00:11:08,101 --> 00:11:10,067
                EUGENE?         
<i>HOW'S HELEN?</i>                    


149
00:11:10,136 --> 00:11:12,069
    HOW'S MY WIFE?              
    HAVE YOU SEEN HER?          


150
00:11:12,139 --> 00:11:15,406
    SON, YOUR WIFE WOULD BE     
    A WHOLE LOT BETTER OFF...   


151
00:11:15,475 --> 00:11:18,943
IF YOU'D JUST STOP THIS NONSENSE
AND BRING YOURSELF IN.          


152
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:22,313
    <i> I CAN'T DO THAT.</i>           
    <i> COLOMBIANS WILL FIND US.</i>   


153
00:11:22,382 --> 00:11:24,882
        THAT'S WHAT JIMMY SAID. 
         THAT'S WHY I RAN.      


154
00:11:24,951 --> 00:11:27,685
I AIN'T STICKIN' MY NECK OUT    
WITH NOBODY STANDIN' BEHIND ME. 


155
00:11:27,754 --> 00:11:32,356
<i>[ Garrison ] YOU FORGET JIMMY.</i>  
<i>THE CARTEL DIDN'T KILL HIM,</i>     
<i>AND YOU KNOW IT.</i>                


156
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:35,960
    - NOW JIMMY ABANDONED YOU.  
    -<i> NO. HE GOT SCARED.</i>        


157
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,862
<i>JIMMY WAS MY BEST FRIEND, MAN.</i>  


158
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:40,331
HE SOLD YOU OUT, EUGENE.        


159
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,599
HE NEVER                        
TOLD YOU ABOUT THE DRUGS,       


160
00:11:42,668 --> 00:11:45,270
<i>AND HE TRIED TO RUN</i>             
<i> AND LEAVE YOU TO TAKE THE RAP.</i> 


161
00:11:45,338 --> 00:11:48,639
    <i> NO. HE MADE A MISTAKE.</i>     
    <i> HE WAS JUST TRYING</i>         
    <i> TO SAVE OUR BUSINESS.</i>      


162
00:11:49,809 --> 00:11:52,110
    LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA         
    LISTEN TO THIS ANYMORE.     


163
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:56,414
YOU LOVED JIMMY,                
DIDN'T YOU?                     


164
00:11:56,483 --> 00:11:58,148
<i>HE WAS LIKE A BROTHER</i>           
<i>TO YOU.</i>                         


165
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:01,352
        -<i> WHO'S THIS?</i>           
        - MY NAME IS JAROD.     


166
00:12:04,023 --> 00:12:07,958
    - IT'S LONELY OUT THERE.    
    - WHAT THE HELL             
      DO YOU KNOW ABOUT IT?     


167
00:12:08,027 --> 00:12:12,230
    YOU'VE BEEN RUNNING,        
    AND YOU'RE SCARED.          


168
00:12:12,298 --> 00:12:15,399
    YOU FEEL LIKE               
     YOU CAN'T TRUST ANYBODY.   


169
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:17,402
            NOBODY'S TELLING YOU
            THE TRUTH.          


170
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:21,506
    <i> [ Sniffling ]</i>              
    <i> I DIDN'T WANT ANY OF THIS.</i> 
<i>I KNOW YOU DIDN'T.</i>              


171
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:25,910
BUT YOU CAN'T RUN FOREVER.      


172
00:12:25,979 --> 00:12:28,880
        BUT IT'S SAFER FOR ME   
        AND FOR HELEN.          


173
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:35,086
    HEY. YOU TELL HER           
    I LOVE HER, JAROD.          


174
00:12:35,154 --> 00:12:36,988
    EUGENE.                     


175
00:12:38,158 --> 00:12:40,357
    - EUGENE.                   
    - PUBLIC PHONE.             


176
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,427
        <i> COLLINSVILLE, TEXAS.</i>   


177
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:55,840
        [ Men Chattering ]      


178
00:12:57,177 --> 00:12:59,277
EUGENE.                         


179
00:13:02,449 --> 00:13:05,850
YOU DON'T HAVE TO RUN           
ANYMORE.                        
                        JAROD?  


180
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:10,187
YES.                            
IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.          


181
00:13:10,256 --> 00:13:12,556
        -<i> [ Lane ]</i>              
         <i> HE'S GOT A GUN!</i>       
        - I PROMISE.            


182
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,158
<i>[ Garrison ]</i>                    
<i>FEDERAL MARSHAL! FREEZE!</i>        


183
00:13:14,226 --> 00:13:17,228
        -<i> [ Gunshots ]</i>          
        - HE'S UNARMED!         


184
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:20,331
-<i> WE'RE MOVING TO YOU, JAROD.</i>   
- HE'S UNARMED!                 


185
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:28,205
<i>DON'T SHOOT!</i>                    
<i> DON'T SHOOT! HE'S UNARMED!</i>     


186
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:30,708
            DON'T SHOOT!        


187
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:39,383
    <i> [ Garrison ]</i>               
    <i> GET AFTER HIM!</i>             


188
00:13:39,452 --> 00:13:42,619
<i>- [ Engine Starts, Revs ]</i>       
<i>- [ Man ] HEY! THAT'S MY BIKE!</i>  


189
00:13:42,688 --> 00:13:48,192
<i> I GOT ONE DEAD DRUG RUNNER,</i>    
<i> A TRIAL SET TO START</i>           
<i> IN 72 HOURS AND NOW THIS!</i>      


190
00:13:52,465 --> 00:13:54,399
        THERE GOES              
        YOUR PERFECT RECORD.    


191
00:14:02,742 --> 00:14:05,142
I'VE BEEN COMBING STATE         
AND FEDERAL DATABASES.          


192
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:08,812
EVERY TIME I GET CLOSE          
TO SOMEONE WITH REMOTELY        
COMPARABLE PARAMETERS,          


193
00:14:08,881 --> 00:14:10,814
I HIT A BRICK WALL.             


194
00:14:10,883 --> 00:14:13,016
        YOU CAN PICK UP WOMEN   
        ON THE COMPUTER,        
        BUT YOU CAN'T DO THIS?  


195
00:14:13,085 --> 00:14:15,620
NO, NOT IF I CAN'T SEND PICTURES
OVER THE INTERNET.              


196
00:14:16,889 --> 00:14:18,822
I'M SORRY.                      
[ Clears Throat ]               


197
00:14:23,062 --> 00:14:25,396
                OKAY.           


198
00:14:25,465 --> 00:14:29,133
         YOU AGE                
        <i> ONE</i> OF THE PHOTOGRAPHS 
         AND SEND IT OUT.       


199
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:34,505
            I WANNA KNOW        
            WHAT THIS IS ABOUT. 


200
00:14:34,573 --> 00:14:36,807
EXCUSE ME?                      


201
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,809
    IT'S JUST THAT              
    I'M RISKING MY NECK HERE,   


202
00:14:38,879 --> 00:14:41,279
        AND I-- I HAVE A RIGHT  
        TO KNOW WHY.            


203
00:14:44,551 --> 00:14:46,484
IT'S ABOUT MY MOTHER.           


204
00:14:46,553 --> 00:14:49,820
THESE CHILDREN MAY HAVE         
HAD SOMETHING TO DO             
WITH HER DEATH.                 


205
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:57,428
SO, HOW'D HE LOOK?              


206
00:14:57,496 --> 00:15:00,865
        LIKE SOMEONE WHO MISSES 
        HIS WIFE A LOT.         


207
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:03,700
    <i> YOU KNOW, THE ONLY THING</i>   
    <i> HE'S WORRIED ABOUT...</i>      


208
00:15:11,878 --> 00:15:13,811
        [ Chuckles ]            


209
00:15:15,948 --> 00:15:19,183
    <i> YOU TWO LOOK VERY HAPPY.</i>   
<i>IT'S OUR HONEYMOON.</i>             


210
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:22,620
BE A YEAR NEXT MONTH.           


211
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:25,889
<i>YOU ALWAYS HEAR</i>                 
<i>ABOUT THOSE PEOPLE THAT</i>         
<i>MARRY THEIR FIRST TRUE LOVE.</i>    


212
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:28,125
WELL, THAT WAS ME               
AND EUGENE.                     


213
00:15:28,193 --> 00:15:31,395
<i>I NEVER EVEN KISSED</i>             
<i>ANOTHER BOY.</i>                    


214
00:15:31,464 --> 00:15:35,332
AFTER THE CEREMONY, WE WENT     
DOWN TO A LITTLE MOTEL          
IN CORPUS CHRISTI.              


215
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:40,537
            LOOKS VERY NICE.    
<i>OH, IT WAS A RATHOLE.</i>           


216
00:15:40,606 --> 00:15:44,475
BUT IT WAS ALL WE COULD AFFORD, 
SO IT'S-- IT'S SPECIAL TO US.   


217
00:15:47,813 --> 00:15:50,547
<i>EUGENE DOESN'T</i>                  
<i>TRUST YOU PEOPLE ANYMORE.</i>       


218
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:52,450
    BECAUSE OF JIMMY RAYFORD?   


219
00:15:52,518 --> 00:15:54,651
THEY WENT TO GRADE SCHOOL       
TOGETHER.                       


220
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,653
SOME OLDER BOYS                 
WERE BEATIN' UP ON EUGENE,      


221
00:15:56,722 --> 00:15:59,856
AND JIMMY CAME IN               
 AND STOOD UP FOR HIM.          


222
00:15:59,925 --> 00:16:04,328
GOT HIS BUTT WHIPPED,           
BUT, UH, HE SAVED EUGENE        
FROM A LOT WORSE.               


223
00:16:04,397 --> 00:16:07,097
I CAN'T TELL YOU                
HOW MANY TIMES                  
I'VE HEARD THAT STORY.          


224
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:10,100
            WELL, THEY WERE     
            BEST FRIENDS.       


225
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:12,102
        FEW THINGS              
        ARE STRONGER THAN THAT. 


226
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:16,774
YEAH. THE ONE PERSON THAT       
EUGENE THOUGHT THAT HE COULD    
ALWAYS TRUST AND BELIEVE IN...  


227
00:16:16,842 --> 00:16:19,242
TURNED HIM INTO A DRUG RUNNER   
AND SOLD HIM OUT.               


228
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:22,779
BUT TO EUGENE,                  
JIMMY WAS EVERYTHING.           


229
00:16:22,848 --> 00:16:25,982
        YOU EVER THINK          
        THAT MAYBE EUGENE       
        WAS RIGHT ABOUT JIMMY?  


230
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:30,720
JIMMY RAYFORD                   
JUMPED OFF THAT PLANE           
BECAUSE HE'S A COWARD.          


231
00:16:30,789 --> 00:16:32,722
[ Scoffs ]                      
HE TRIED TO HANG                
EVERYTHING ON EUGENE.           


232
00:16:32,791 --> 00:16:35,159
THAT'S WHAT KIND                
OF BEST FRIEND HE WAS.          


233
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:40,931
                MRS. DIGGS,     


234
00:16:42,101 --> 00:16:44,435
        TWO FEDERAL MARSHALS,   


235
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:47,538
        THEY OPENED FIRE        
        ON YOUR HUSBAND TODAY.  


236
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:49,540
            THEY MISSED.        


237
00:16:49,609 --> 00:16:52,609
        NEXT TIME, HE MIGHT NOT 
        BE SO LUCKY.            


238
00:16:54,047 --> 00:16:56,947
                    [ Sighs ]   
                    HELP ME...  


239
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:00,885
        SO I CAN HELP EUGENE.   


240
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:10,193
THERE'S A PAY PHONE.            


241
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:14,331
    HE CALLS ME.                


242
00:17:15,735 --> 00:17:19,703
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>I HAVE NEVER BEEN</i>               
<i>SO AFRAID, DR. SHAFTON.</i>         


243
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:22,339
    IS THIS ABOUT MR. RAINES?   


244
00:17:23,742 --> 00:17:26,676
        [ Exhales ]             


245
00:17:26,745 --> 00:17:29,013
    EVERYWHERE HE GOES,         


246
00:17:29,081 --> 00:17:31,415
    EVERYTHING HE TOUCHES--     


247
00:17:31,483 --> 00:17:34,885
DISHONESTY, MALICE.             


248
00:17:34,954 --> 00:17:36,987
        WELL, WHY HAVEN'T YOU   
        CONFRONTED HIM?         


249
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:38,989
<i>RAINES IS A DANGEROUS MAN.</i>      


250
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:44,661
HE MAY BE INVOLVED              
WITH THE MURDER                 
OF MISS PARKER'S MOTHER.        


251
00:17:46,165 --> 00:17:49,332
AND THAT ACCIDENT THAT PUT      
MY BROTHER IN THE COMA?         


252
00:17:50,536 --> 00:17:53,537
IT MAY NOT HAVE BEEN            
AN ACCIDENT AT ALL.             


253
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:57,174
                [ Scoffs ]      


254
00:17:58,711 --> 00:18:01,011
            NOW-- YOU'RE MAKING 
            EXCUSES, SYDNEY.    


255
00:18:02,147 --> 00:18:07,551
I FANTASIZE ABOUT KILLING--     
KILLING HIM.                    


256
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:13,957
        NOW WE'VE GOT LESS      
        THAN 48 HOURS...        


257
00:18:14,026 --> 00:18:16,693
        BEFORE THE GRAND JURY   
        CONVENES.               


258
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:19,763
        I WANT DIGGS            
        BACK WHERE HE BELONGS,  


259
00:18:19,832 --> 00:18:21,765
        READY TO TESTIFY.       


260
00:18:26,004 --> 00:18:27,705
I HAVE TO FIND HIM.             


261
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:30,874
    WHY? SO YOU CAN PUT         
    A BULLET THROUGH HIS HEAD?  


262
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,109
HE'S A FUGITIVE.                
                    HE'S A KID. 


263
00:18:33,178 --> 00:18:35,879
HE REACHED FOR A GUN.           
                THAT'S A LIE,   
                AND YOU KNOW IT.


264
00:18:39,986 --> 00:18:41,986
            WHY IS THIS CASE    
            SO PERSONAL TO YOU? 


265
00:18:43,822 --> 00:18:47,691
        I CHECKED THE FILE.     
        THERE'S NO CONNECTION   
        BETWEEN YOU AND DIGGS.  


266
00:18:49,561 --> 00:18:52,596
        WHAT HAPPENED THE NIGHT 
        THAT JIMMY RAYFORD DIED?


267
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:57,635
    IT WAS MY FAULT.            
    THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.       


268
00:19:02,274 --> 00:19:05,676
I WENT UP INTO THE COCKPIT      
TO CALL IN A REPORT.            


269
00:19:05,745 --> 00:19:09,479
NEXT THING I KNOW,              
CABIN PRESSURE'S GONE...        


270
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:11,481
<i>AND GARRISON'S LAYIN' THERE</i>     
<i>ALL CUT UP.</i>                     


271
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:14,785
            LANE! HELP ME!      


272
00:19:14,854 --> 00:19:19,989
BOB GARRISON GAVE ME MY BREAK   
INTO THE MARSHALS,              
AND I LET HIM DOWN.             


273
00:19:20,058 --> 00:19:22,125
HE'S NOT JUST MY BOSS.          


274
00:19:22,194 --> 00:19:24,495
    HE'S MY FRIEND.             


275
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:31,701
<i>WE FOUND HIM, SYDNEY.</i>           
<i>WE FOUND HIM ON THE</i>             
<i>SUBLEVEL ELEVATOR GOIN' DOWN.</i>   


276
00:19:32,772 --> 00:19:34,838
    YOU CAN'T ESCAPE FROM THERE.


277
00:19:34,907 --> 00:19:38,275
I WASN'T TRYING TO ESCAPE.      
 I WAS TRYING TO FIND MY FRIEND.


278
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:40,344
                [ Sighs ]       
                JAROD.          


279
00:19:40,412 --> 00:19:43,480
I JUST KNOW, IF I SAW HIM ONCE, 
 I KNOW HE'D BE MY FRIEND.      


280
00:19:43,549 --> 00:19:45,282
    I DON'T HAVE THE AUTHORITY. 


281
00:19:46,618 --> 00:19:48,985
I'M JUST TIRED OF BEING ALONE,  


282
00:19:49,054 --> 00:19:52,522
<i>TIRED OF NOT HAVING</i>             
<i>ANYBODY TO TALK TO.</i>             


283
00:19:52,591 --> 00:19:56,026
IF I HAD A FRIEND,              
I'D DO ANYTHING FOR HIM.        


284
00:20:15,481 --> 00:20:19,316
<i>[ Garrison On Videotape ]</i>       
<i>COME ON, JIMMY. WE'VE BEEN</i>      
<i>TALKING HERE FOR 15 HOURS.</i>      


285
00:20:19,385 --> 00:20:21,585
[ Rayford On Videotape ]        
IF I CUT A DEAL WITH YOU GUYS,  


286
00:20:21,654 --> 00:20:25,723
<i>YOU GOTTA PROMISE ME</i>            
<i>EUGENE'S GONNA BE OKAY.</i>         


287
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:28,125
HE DIDN'T KNOW ANYTHING.        


288
00:20:30,295 --> 00:20:32,930
I GOT HIM INTO THIS.            
I GOTTA DO RIGHT BY HIM,        
YOU KNOW?                       


289
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,567
<i>I'LL TAKE THE PRISON TIME.</i>      


290
00:20:38,037 --> 00:20:42,038
<i>YOU JUST GOTTA PROTECT EUGENE</i>   
<i>FROM THE COLOMBIANS.</i>            


291
00:20:46,845 --> 00:20:49,045
    HE'S MY FRIEND.             


292
00:20:49,114 --> 00:20:53,150
<i>[ Young Jarod's Voice ]</i>         
<i>IF I HAD A FRIEND,</i>              
<i>I'D DO ANYTHING FOR HIM.</i>        


293
00:20:55,955 --> 00:21:00,090
SO, AGENT CODY, IS THIS         
YOUR IDEA OF A BRIBE?           


294
00:21:00,159 --> 00:21:02,125
        NOW WHY WOULD I WANT    
        TO BRIBE YOU?           


295
00:21:02,194 --> 00:21:05,696
BECAUSE YOU THINK               
I'VE BEEN TALKING TO EUGENE.    


296
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:08,565
    - I DO WANNA TALK TO YOU    
      ABOUT THE CASE.           
    - TALK.                     


297
00:21:08,634 --> 00:21:11,067
I GOT A COPY                    
OF JIMMY RAYFORD'S CONFESSION.  


298
00:21:11,136 --> 00:21:13,570
        HOW THE HELL            
        DID YOU GET THAT?       


299
00:21:13,639 --> 00:21:16,573
        I PRETENDED TO BE       
        A FEDERAL PROSECUTOR    
        ASSIGNED TO THE CASE.   


300
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:20,477
                I'M KIDDING.    
                GARRISON HAD IT.


301
00:21:20,546 --> 00:21:22,746
    SO?                         


302
00:21:22,814 --> 00:21:27,251
    <i> SO, JIMMY RAYFORD ASKED</i>    
    <i> FOR A TOUGHER SENTENCE</i>     
    <i> FROM THE U.S. ATTORNEY...</i>  


303
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:31,488
WITH THE CONDITION              
THAT EUGENE GOT                 
A WITNESS PROTECTION PROGRAM.   


304
00:21:31,557 --> 00:21:35,058
    - EUGENE GOT IT, CORRECT?   
    - YEAH.                     


305
00:21:35,126 --> 00:21:37,060
    SO WHY WOULD JIMMY RAYFORD  
    ATTACK A U.S. MARSHAL...    


306
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:40,764
    AND JUMP OUT OF AN AIRPLANE 
    IF HE HAD WHAT HE WANTED?   


307
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:43,399
HAVE YOU EVER SPENT ANY TIME    
IN A FEDERAL PRISON?            


308
00:21:43,468 --> 00:21:46,837
    - SOME.                     
    - SO THEN YOU KNOW IT'S--   
      IT'S NO CLUB MED.         


309
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:50,740
    SO YOU'RE SAYING            
    THAT JIMMY RAYFORD RAN...   


310
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:53,176
        BECAUSE HE WANTED       
        TO AVOID JAIL TIME.     


311
00:21:53,245 --> 00:21:55,178
        THAT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.


312
00:21:55,247 --> 00:21:57,581
WELL, TELL THAT TO GARRISON.    


313
00:21:57,650 --> 00:22:00,284
HE'S THE ONE WHO TOOK           
75 STITCHES IN THE BACK.        


314
00:22:00,352 --> 00:22:02,353
                [ Exhales ]     


315
00:22:31,283 --> 00:22:33,217
[ Videocassette Engages ]       


316
00:22:34,654 --> 00:22:39,489
AGENT LANE HAD GONE             
TO THE FORWARD CABIN            
TO RADIO AHEAD.                 


317
00:22:39,558 --> 00:22:41,625
<i>THE PRISONER ASKED</i>              
<i>TO USE THE RESTROOM.</i>            


318
00:22:41,694 --> 00:22:45,195
ONCE WE WERE IN                 
THE REAR OF THE PLANE,          
HE BENT TO TIE HIS SHOE...      


319
00:22:46,598 --> 00:22:49,800
<i>AND RETRIEVED A HOMEMADE KNIFE</i>  
<i>FROM HIS SOCK.</i>                  


320
00:22:49,869 --> 00:22:53,536
HE REACHED UP                   
FROM A BENT POSITION            
AND LUNGED AT ME.               


321
00:22:53,605 --> 00:22:55,572
<i>LUNGED AT ME.</i>                   
<i>AND LUNGED AT ME.</i>               


322
00:22:55,641 --> 00:22:59,843
<i>I MADE A DEFENSIVE MOVE,</i>        
<i>BUT HE CAUGHT ME IN THE BACK</i>    
<i>WITH A DOWNWARD MOVEMENT.</i>       


323
00:22:59,911 --> 00:23:01,979
CAUGHT ME IN THE BACK           
WITH A DOWNWARD MOVEMENT.       


324
00:23:02,048 --> 00:23:04,314
<i>CAUGHT ME IN THE BACK</i>           
<i>WITH A DOWNWARD MOVEMENT.</i>       


325
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:08,251
<i>YOU CAN SEE THE POINT OF IMPACT</i> 
<i>FROM THE CUT IN MY SHIRT.</i>       


326
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:11,187
<i>I WENT DOWN IMMEDIATELY,</i>        
<i>AND THAT'S WHEN</i>                 
<i>THE PRISONER ESCAPED.</i>           


327
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:26,669
REACHED UP FROM A BENT POSITION 
AND LUNGED AT ME.               


328
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:30,840
<i>I MADE A DEFENSIVE MOVE,</i>        
<i>BUT HE CAUGHT ME IN THE BACK</i>    
<i>WITH A DOWNWARD MOVEMENT.</i>       


329
00:23:32,444 --> 00:23:36,346
<i>YOU CAN SEE THE POINT OF IMPACT</i> 
<i>FROM THE CUT IN MY SHIRT.</i>       


330
00:23:36,414 --> 00:23:39,916
<i>I WENT DOWN IMMEDIATELY,</i>        
<i>AND THAT'S WHEN</i>                 
<i>THE PRISONER ESCAPED.</i>           


331
00:23:41,654 --> 00:23:45,588
THIS IS A TERRIBLE TRAGEDY FOR  
THE ENTIRE MARSHAL'S SERVICE.   


332
00:23:49,394 --> 00:23:53,530
WELL, GARRISON, LOOKS LIKE      
YOU STABBED YOURSELF            
IN THE BACK THIS TIME.          


333
00:24:15,154 --> 00:24:17,688
[ No Audible Dialogue ]         


334
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:31,535
    ARE YOU SURE NOBODY'S BEEN  
    MONITORING YOUR TERMINAL?   


335
00:24:32,871 --> 00:24:35,639
[ Exhales ]                     
AS SURE AS ANYTHING             
GETS AROUND HERE.               


336
00:24:35,707 --> 00:24:40,076
UH, I DISCONNECTED THE LINK     
FROM THE CENTRE MAINFRAME.      


337
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:42,746
THIS BABY, UH,                  
SHOULD BE FLYING SOLO.          


338
00:24:42,815 --> 00:24:44,748
[ Keyboarding ]                 


339
00:24:46,552 --> 00:24:48,618
    ARE THOSE THE SAME CLOTHES  
    YOU WERE WEARING YESTERDAY? 


340
00:24:49,622 --> 00:24:51,555
OH. YEAH.                       


341
00:24:51,624 --> 00:24:54,324
I'VE BEEN RUNNING FACES         
AGAINST THE D.M.V. FILES        
ACROSS THE COUNTRY...           


342
00:24:54,393 --> 00:24:57,761
FOR, LIKE, THE LAST 16 HOURS,   
AND-- [ Clears Throat ]         


343
00:24:57,830 --> 00:25:03,433
I CAME UP WITH DARA LANDERS--   
32, LIVES IN SUBURBAN MILWAUKEE.


344
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:06,203
    - ADDRESS?                  
    - [ Clears Throat ] OH.     


345
00:25:11,276 --> 00:25:16,380
<i>I, UH, HOPE THIS HELPS YOU FIND</i> 
<i>THE TRUTH YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.</i>   


346
00:25:19,852 --> 00:25:21,918
        THANK YOU.              


347
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:27,090
        AND TAKE A BATH,        
        WOULD YOU, BROOTS?      


348
00:25:32,064 --> 00:25:33,996
    MM.                         


349
00:25:34,065 --> 00:25:37,033
<i>♪♪ [ Country ]</i>                  
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>TRY TO KEEP HIM CALM.</i>           


350
00:25:37,102 --> 00:25:39,302
[ Rings ]                       


351
00:25:41,406 --> 00:25:45,975
    - HELEN.                    
    - EUGENE. I WANT YOU        
      TO COME HOME, BABY.       


352
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:50,546
I MISS YOU SO MUCH.             
THIS DOESN'T MAKE               
MUCH SENSE ANYMORE.             


353
00:25:50,616 --> 00:25:54,417
    LISTEN, I KNOW.             
    BUT I CAN'T TRUST           
    THESE PEOPLE ANYMORE.       


354
00:25:56,088 --> 00:25:59,522
    THEY TRIED                  
    TO KILL ME, HELEN.          


355
00:25:59,591 --> 00:26:01,692
IF THEY EVEN KNEW WHERE I WAS-- 
 IF THEY EVEN KNEW--            


356
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:03,827
        WE'D NEVER              
        SEE EACH OTHER AGAIN.   


357
00:26:03,896 --> 00:26:07,631
EUGENE, THEY MIGHT ALREADY KNOW.
    WHY?                        


358
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:09,799
            WHAT ARE YOU        
            TALKIN' ABOUT?      


359
00:26:09,868 --> 00:26:12,903
YOU DIDN'T TELL 'EM             
ABOUT ME CALLIN' YOU?           
    I'M SORRY, HONEY.           


360
00:26:12,971 --> 00:26:15,172
    YOU TOLD 'EM I CALLED YOU?  
    WHY?                        


361
00:26:15,241 --> 00:26:18,541
        'CAUSE I'M AFRAID.      
        THAT'S--                


362
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:23,379
    YOU SOLD ME OUT, GIRL.      
    I CANNOT BELIEVE YOU        
    DID THAT TO ME, HELEN.      


363
00:26:23,448 --> 00:26:25,381
        YOU JUST SOLD ME OUT.   


364
00:26:25,450 --> 00:26:28,518
BUT WE CAN TRUST JAROD.         


365
00:26:28,587 --> 00:26:31,688
[ Line Clicks ]                 


366
00:26:31,757 --> 00:26:34,991
I SHOULDN'T HAVE DONE THIS.     
HE'S SCARED, AND I DON'T KNOW   
WHERE HE'S GONNA GO.            


367
00:26:35,060 --> 00:26:38,161
        HE'S GONNA GO           
        WHERE HE FEELS SAFE,    


368
00:26:39,698 --> 00:26:41,899
LIKE MAYBE A HONEYMOON MOTEL.   


369
00:26:46,405 --> 00:26:48,371
<i>SYDNEY.</i>                         


370
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,974
WOULD YOU TELL ME MORE          
ABOUT THESE...                  


371
00:26:51,043 --> 00:26:53,609
VIOLENT FANTASIES               
YOU'VE BEEN HAVING?             


372
00:26:55,047 --> 00:26:57,513
        I THINK ABOUT           
        WHAT RAINES DID.        


373
00:27:01,319 --> 00:27:03,720
            TAKE ANGELO.        


374
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:07,791
        ANGELO WAS MY PROJECT-- 
        VERY SPECIAL.           


375
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:14,597
            THAT IS UNTIL       
            RAINES TWISTED HIM  
            INTO SOMETHING ELSE.


376
00:27:14,666 --> 00:27:19,602
            <i> WHEN I THINK OF ALL</i>
            <i> THE INNOCENT MINDS</i> 
            <i> HE HAS DESTROYED.</i>  


377
00:27:22,007 --> 00:27:25,475
CAN'T YOU SOLICIT HELP          
FROM SOMEONE FROM THE CENTRE--  
THE DIRECTOR?                   


378
00:27:28,313 --> 00:27:30,447
            I CANNOT TRUST HER. 


379
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:35,084
    I CANNOT TRUST ANYONE       
    OF AUTHORITY AT THE CENTRE. 


380
00:27:38,123 --> 00:27:40,123
WHAT ABOUT MISS PARKER?         


381
00:27:41,593 --> 00:27:44,127
        SHE DIGS INTO MATTERS   
         SHE SHOULDN'T.         


382
00:27:44,196 --> 00:27:48,966
<i>I'VE WARNED HER SEVERAL TIMES,</i>  
<i>BUT SHE WON'T LISTEN TO ME.</i>     


383
00:27:49,034 --> 00:27:50,800
HOW DOES THAT MAKE YOU FEEL?    


384
00:27:50,869 --> 00:27:53,570
        ANGRY! HELPLESS!        


385
00:27:56,342 --> 00:27:58,275
<i>WHAT ELSE?</i>                      


386
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:04,947
WHAT ELSE, SYDNEY?              


387
00:28:15,761 --> 00:28:18,194
        I CAN'T TAKE MUCH MORE. 


388
00:28:33,145 --> 00:28:35,645
                <i> [ Footsteps ]</i>  


389
00:28:38,383 --> 00:28:40,383
[ Door Opens ]                  


390
00:28:40,451 --> 00:28:44,787
    - IT'S ME. IT'S JAROD.      
    - YOU ALMOST GOT ME KILLED, 
      JAROD.                    


391
00:28:44,856 --> 00:28:47,657
I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH THAT.  
 I PROMISE YOU.                 


392
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:52,028
YEAH, WELL, YOUR LAST PROMISE   
NEARLY GOT MY HEAD BLOWN OFF,   
MAN.                            


393
00:28:52,097 --> 00:28:54,030
        <i> LOOK, I UNDERSTAND</i>     
        <i> WHY YOU FEEL THAT WAY.</i> 


394
00:28:54,099 --> 00:28:57,233
    BUT YOU HAVE TO TRUST ME.   


395
00:28:57,302 --> 00:29:02,072
YOU PEOPLE CAN'T PROTECT ME,    
SO I DON'T NEED YOU ANYMORE.    


396
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:04,875
I DON'T NEED ANYBODY ANYMORE.   


397
00:29:04,943 --> 00:29:07,143
        WELL, THERE'S SOMEBODY  
        THAT REALLY NEEDS YOU.  


398
00:29:11,116 --> 00:29:13,049
<i>[ Switch Clicks ]</i>               


399
00:29:24,429 --> 00:29:27,096
                YOU SHOULDN'T   
                HAVE TOLD HIM.  


400
00:29:27,165 --> 00:29:29,098
                YOU SHOULD'VE   
                TRUSTED ME...   


401
00:29:29,167 --> 00:29:32,001
    THE WAY I TRUSTED YOU,      
     THE WAY I TRUSTED JIMMY.   


402
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:36,239
I'M SORRY.                      
I WAS AFRAID, HONEY.            
        SO YOU BRING HIM HERE?  


403
00:29:36,308 --> 00:29:39,609
NO. NO, HE'S NOT                
LIKE THE OTHERS.                
YOU CAN BELIEVE HIM.            


404
00:29:39,678 --> 00:29:41,611
I SWEAR.                        
 I SWEAR.                       


405
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:46,115
    OH.                         
    [ Crying ]                  


406
00:29:51,523 --> 00:29:53,523
WELCOME HOME.                   


407
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:01,965
        WHAT THE HELL           
        ARE YOU DOIN', JAROD?   


408
00:30:03,902 --> 00:30:08,437
    YOU MOVE WITHOUT ME?        
    YOU PUT A CIVILIAN          
    INTO A VOLATILE SITUATION?  


409
00:30:11,343 --> 00:30:15,378
<i>WHAT'S IMPORTANT</i>                
<i>IS EUGENE IS HERE,</i>              
<i>AND HE'S STILL YOUR WITNESS.</i>    


410
00:30:15,447 --> 00:30:19,148
NOW, TOMORROW MORNING,          
WE GET ON THAT PLANE,           
AND WE TAKE DOWN THE CARTEL.    


411
00:30:19,217 --> 00:30:24,287
    YEAH? WELL, HE MOVES        
    FIRST THING IN THE MORNIN'. 
    YOU GOT THAT?               


412
00:30:30,295 --> 00:30:32,895
            BRING IN THE WIFE-- 
            SMART MOVE.         


413
00:30:32,964 --> 00:30:38,367
WHEN YOU'RE ON THE RUN,         
PEOPLE YOU LOVE--               
PEOPLE YOU MISS--               


414
00:30:38,436 --> 00:30:40,904
THEY'RE THE MOST IMPORTANT      
THINGS TO YOU.                  


415
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:51,647
<i>[ Latino Man On Phone ] WHAT</i>    
<i>THE HELL ARE WE PAYING YOU FOR?</i> 
<i>YOU DON'T COME CHEAP, MARSHAL.</i>  


416
00:30:51,716 --> 00:30:55,218
        <i> BOTH OF THESE WITNESSES</i>
        <i> SHOULD HAVE BEEN</i>       
        <i> TAKEN CARE OF BY NOW.</i>  


417
00:30:55,287 --> 00:30:57,220
            MY CLIENT IS PLEASED
            ABOUT JIMMY RAYFORD,


418
00:30:57,289 --> 00:31:00,322
    BUT DIGGS WAS NEVER SUPPOSED
    TO BE BROUGHT IN ALIVE.     


419
00:31:01,659 --> 00:31:05,695
WELL, THERE WERE SOME           
UNFORESEEN COMPLICATIONS THERE. 


420
00:31:05,764 --> 00:31:08,531
[ Latino Man ]                  
IT DOESN'T MATTER.              
THAT PLANE WILL LAND,           


421
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:11,701
BUT IT WILL BE                  
IN A MILLION PIECES             
WHEN IT DOES.                   


422
00:31:11,770 --> 00:31:14,136
[ Garrison ]                    
THAT'S WHAT THIS                
REMOTE CONTROL IS FOR, RIGHT?   


423
00:31:14,205 --> 00:31:16,372
IT WILL DISABLE                 
THE ELECTRICAL SYSTEM.          


424
00:31:16,441 --> 00:31:20,142
WHATEVER YOU SAY.               
                    <i> [ Beep ]</i>   


425
00:31:32,557 --> 00:31:35,191
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>              


426
00:31:38,463 --> 00:31:42,364
            HELLO. I'M LOOKING  
            FOR DARA LANDERS.   


427
00:31:43,568 --> 00:31:45,635
I THOUGHT ONE DAY               
YOU MIGHT COME.                 


428
00:31:45,703 --> 00:31:49,505
    - MIGHT COME?               
    - YOU'RE DARA'S SISTER,     
      AREN'T YOU?               


429
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:54,477
            HER SISTER?         
<i>YOU LOOK JUST LIKE THE WOMAN</i>    
<i>WHO GAVE DARA UP FOR ADOPTION.</i>  


430
00:31:54,546 --> 00:31:56,312
HER NAME WAS CATHERINE.         


431
00:31:56,381 --> 00:31:59,815
                PARKER.         
<i>I'M NOT SURE.</i>                   


432
00:31:59,884 --> 00:32:02,919
THE LAWYER WAS THE ONLY ONE     
WHO KNEW HER LAST NAME.         


433
00:32:02,987 --> 00:32:06,088
        MAY I SPEAK WITH DARA?  


434
00:32:08,092 --> 00:32:10,326
    I ASSUMED YOU KNEW.         


435
00:32:12,496 --> 00:32:15,999
    DARA PASSED AWAY            
    TWO MONTHS AGO.             


436
00:32:22,907 --> 00:32:24,974
DARA WAS A GIFTED CHILD.        


437
00:32:25,043 --> 00:32:27,276
SHE GRADUATED COLLEGE AT 17.    


438
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:33,415
SHE LOVED THE THEATER,          
PLAYING THE DIFFERENT ROLES.    


439
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:36,853
EVEN WHEN SHE                   
WAS A LITTLE GIRL,              


440
00:32:36,921 --> 00:32:41,057
<i>SHE WOULD MAKE UP</i>               
<i>AN ENTIRE WORLD...</i>              


441
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:43,059
<i>AND THEN LOSE HERSELF IN IT.</i>    


442
00:32:46,497 --> 00:32:49,565
            SHE SEEMED TO HAVE  
            A VERY HAPPY LIFE.  


443
00:32:50,668 --> 00:32:52,669
    WE WANTED TO GIVE HER       
    THE BEST...                 


444
00:32:52,737 --> 00:32:55,038
    THAT ANY CHILD              
    COULD POSSIBLY HAVE.        


445
00:33:01,012 --> 00:33:03,780
        THE LAWYER WHO          
        ARRANGED THE ADOPTION,  


446
00:33:03,848 --> 00:33:05,948
        DO YOU KNOW HIS NAME?   


447
00:33:06,017 --> 00:33:08,584
        STEINMAN.               
        MM, NO.                 


448
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:12,321
    UH, "BERG." STEINBERG.      
    MICHAEL STEINBERG. YES.     


449
00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:16,125
            DO YOU KNOW WHERE   
            I MIGHT FIND HIM?   
<i>I'M SORRY.</i>                      


450
00:33:16,194 --> 00:33:18,294
HE MOVED AWAY WITHOUT A WORD.   


451
00:33:18,362 --> 00:33:21,630
UM, I THINK                     
IT WAS BACK IN '82.             


452
00:33:24,135 --> 00:33:28,470
        AND YOU HAD NO FURTHER  
        CONTACT WITH MY MOTHER? 
<i>NO.</i>                             


453
00:33:28,539 --> 00:33:33,209
<i>NO, BUT I REMEMBER</i>              
<i>THAT MR. STEINBERG SAID...</i>      


454
00:33:33,277 --> 00:33:37,780
<i>SHE HAD A DREAM</i>                 
<i>OF MOVING TO EUROPE,</i>            


455
00:33:37,849 --> 00:33:41,985
OF GIVING HER LITTLE DAUGHTER   
A BETTER LIFE.                  


456
00:33:44,055 --> 00:33:46,688
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN YOU.        


457
00:33:51,963 --> 00:33:53,996
            IF I MAY ASK,       


458
00:33:56,234 --> 00:33:58,301
            HOW DID DARA--      


459
00:33:59,704 --> 00:34:01,637
        SURGERY.                


460
00:34:03,842 --> 00:34:05,842
    REMOVING HER APPENDIX.      


461
00:34:08,946 --> 00:34:11,146
ONE MINUTE, SHE WAS JUST FINE.  


462
00:34:13,685 --> 00:34:15,618
    AND THE NEXT MINUTE--       


463
00:34:34,472 --> 00:34:36,572
            WHAT'S THIS?        


464
00:34:37,642 --> 00:34:40,776
    OH, UH, DARA HAD IT WHEN--  


465
00:34:40,845 --> 00:34:43,112
    WHEN YOUR MOTHER            
    BROUGHT HER TO US.          


466
00:34:52,156 --> 00:34:54,089
<i>YOU CAN HAVE IT IF YOU LIKE.</i>    


467
00:34:55,793 --> 00:34:58,727
WE WANTED ALL OF DARA'S FRIENDS 
TO HAVE A MEMENTO.              


468
00:35:01,999 --> 00:35:03,933
                THANK YOU.      


469
00:35:40,505 --> 00:35:43,472
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>


470
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:45,474
JAROD HERE.                     
            IT'S HELEN.         


471
00:35:45,543 --> 00:35:48,444
- I-I'M WORRIED ABOUT EUGENE.   
- HELEN, DON'T WORRY.           


472
00:35:48,513 --> 00:35:50,446
THERE IS NO WAY THAT EUGENE     
IS GETTING ON THAT PLANE.       


473
00:35:50,515 --> 00:35:53,716
    GARRISON AND LANE           
    JUST TOOK HIM.              
    THEY'RE FLYING HIM TONIGHT. 


474
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:38,161
            [ Beeping ]         


475
00:36:41,466 --> 00:36:44,200
LOOKS LIKE SOMEONE'S            
ENTERED THE CARGO AREA.         
            <i> [ Beeping Stops ]</i>  


476
00:36:52,577 --> 00:36:54,510
            [ Beeps ]           


477
00:36:54,579 --> 00:36:59,015
    BOSS, SOMETHIN'S UP.        
    THE PILOT JUST BUZZED ME.   


478
00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:01,617
        HE GOT A WARNING LIGHT. 
        SOMEONE MAY HAVE        
        ACCESSED THE PLANE.     


479
00:37:01,685 --> 00:37:03,352
WHERE?                          


480
00:37:12,997 --> 00:37:15,030
                <i> [ Clattering ]</i> 


481
00:37:16,967 --> 00:37:18,801
                HEADS UP, LANE. 


482
00:37:21,272 --> 00:37:24,006
<i>SEE ANYTHING?</i>                   


483
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:28,478
THERE'S NOBODY DOWN THERE,      
BUT THERE'S A PANEL OPEN.       


484
00:37:28,546 --> 00:37:30,813
    - WHERE'S THE ACCESS HATCH? 
    - IT'S IN THE BACK.         


485
00:37:30,882 --> 00:37:34,417
    - YOU STAY HERE.            
    - NO. I'M COMIN' WITH YOU.  


486
00:37:34,485 --> 00:37:36,352
YOU REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED      
THE LAST TIME.                  


487
00:37:41,826 --> 00:37:43,992
        YOU DIDN'T KNOW         
        WHEN TO LET GO, KID.    


488
00:37:45,763 --> 00:37:47,696
    WHAT'S GOIN' ON?            


489
00:37:54,271 --> 00:37:56,973
EVERYTHING'S FINE.              
STAY IN YOUR SEATS.             
THANK YOU.                      


490
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:09,451
GIVE ME YOUR PIECE.             
 GIVE ME YOUR PIECE, BOY!       


491
00:38:12,289 --> 00:38:14,757
<i>THAT-A-BOY.</i>                     


492
00:38:17,195 --> 00:38:19,728
        IS THIS WHAT HAPPENED   
        TO JIMMY RAYFORD?       


493
00:38:19,797 --> 00:38:23,199
YOU JUST DUMP HIM AT 30,000 FEET
BECAUSE HE WAS GONNA            
TELL THE TRUTH?                 


494
00:38:23,267 --> 00:38:26,269
THE TRUTH DON'T PAY             
AS WELL AS IT USED TO.          


495
00:38:26,337 --> 00:38:29,105
NOW, I PUSH THIS BUTTON--       


496
00:38:29,174 --> 00:38:32,074
TWO MINUTES LATER, THIS PLANE   
BECOMES A FIREBALL...           


497
00:38:32,143 --> 00:38:35,210
SPREAD ALL OVER                 
THE OKLAHOMA COUNTRYSIDE.       


498
00:38:39,183 --> 00:38:42,218
    <i> [ Struggling, Grunting ]</i>   


499
00:38:48,826 --> 00:38:50,826
        WAIT HERE.              


500
00:39:12,750 --> 00:39:15,184
    GOOD MOVE, PARTNER.         


501
00:39:15,253 --> 00:39:17,853
                [ Gasps ]       
                WHY?            


502
00:39:17,921 --> 00:39:20,522
    [ Out Of Breath ]           
    ECONOMICS.                  


503
00:39:20,591 --> 00:39:23,158
THERE'S NO MONEY DEFENDING      
THE JIMMY RAYFORDS OF THE WORLD.


504
00:39:24,729 --> 00:39:27,530
            GRAB THE PARACHUTE. 


505
00:39:27,599 --> 00:39:29,798
                TAKE THE REMOTE.
                HERE.           


506
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:33,035
<i>NO. HERE.</i>                       


507
00:39:37,074 --> 00:39:39,075
                BITCH.          


508
00:39:39,143 --> 00:39:41,544
        [ Gasping ]             
        BITCH.                  


509
00:39:41,612 --> 00:39:44,380
<i>SEE, JAROD? FRIENDS</i>             
<i>WILL BURN YOU EVERY TIME.</i>       


510
00:39:45,583 --> 00:39:47,549
                    [ Grunts ]  


511
00:39:48,453 --> 00:39:51,320
            - [ Beeping ]       
            - NO!               


512
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:53,322
[ Airplane Losing Altitude ]    


513
00:39:53,390 --> 00:39:55,691
        ELECTRICAL SYSTEMS OUT! 
        GO TO RESERVE!          


514
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:59,695
MAYDAY! MAYDAY! THIS IS         
U.S. MARSHAL FLIGHT 1701.       


515
00:39:59,764 --> 00:40:03,666
WE'VE LOST FLIGHT CONTROL.      
I REPEAT.                       
WE'VE LOST FLIGHT CONTROL.      


516
00:40:03,735 --> 00:40:05,735
COVER HER.                      


517
00:40:09,206 --> 00:40:11,206
                    JAROD.      
GARRISON AND MICHAELS           
ARE WORKING TOGETHER.           


518
00:40:11,275 --> 00:40:13,208
I'LL EXPLAIN LATER.             
                    WHAT ARE YOU
                    GONNA DO?   


519
00:40:13,278 --> 00:40:15,878
TELL THE PILOT TO GET READY     
TO PULL UP HARD.                


520
00:40:15,946 --> 00:40:18,714
WE'VE GOT ONE MINUTE TOPS!      


521
00:40:32,663 --> 00:40:37,366
    [ Alarm Beeping ]           
WE'VE GOT 30 SECONDS!           


522
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:39,835
<i>YOU GOT 30 SECONDS, JAROD.</i>      


523
00:40:52,784 --> 00:40:55,551
FIFTEEN SECONDS!                


524
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:59,054
<i>[ Lane ]</i>                        
<i>WE GOT 15 SECONDS!</i>              


525
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:23,879
    - YES!                      
    - [ Laughs ] ALL RIGHT.     


526
00:41:23,948 --> 00:41:25,914
            [ Exhales ]         
            WELL.               


527
00:41:28,119 --> 00:41:30,886
    I ALWAYS KNEW               
    THAT WOULD COME IN HANDY.   


528
00:41:38,496 --> 00:41:40,829
        [ Exhales ]             


529
00:41:44,969 --> 00:41:49,138
<i>WELL, LOOKS LIKE WE FINALLY</i>     
<i>GOT THE SHACKLES</i>                
<i>ON THE RIGHT PERSON.</i>            


530
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,614
<i>[ Hushed ]</i>                      
<i>MISS PARKER.</i>                    


531
00:41:59,684 --> 00:42:03,418
    - I'M PACKING IN THE SEARCH.
      I'M OUT OF IT.            
    - WHY?                      


532
00:42:03,487 --> 00:42:06,955
I GOT RESULTS                   
ON SOME OF THE OTHER NAMES      
FROM YOUR MOTHER'S FILES.       


533
00:42:07,024 --> 00:42:10,959
    - MOST OF THEM ARE DEAD.    
    - DON'T YOU FALL APART      
      ON ME NOW, BROOTS.        


534
00:42:11,028 --> 00:42:14,430
    NO. YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.   
    THEY DIED OF SUDDEN,        
    UNEXPLAINED ILLNESSES--     


535
00:42:14,499 --> 00:42:16,432
        ALL WITHIN              
        THE LAST SIX MONTHS.    


536
00:42:16,501 --> 00:42:19,634
        OH, MY GOD.             
    YES.                        


537
00:42:19,703 --> 00:42:24,006
        THIS IS BAD.            
         THIS IS... VERY--      
<i>[ Shuffling, Squeaking ]</i>        


538
00:42:24,075 --> 00:42:27,242
        I GOTTA GO.             
        <i> [ Cell Phone Beeps ]</i>   


539
00:42:29,814 --> 00:42:32,915
YOU LOOK UPSET, MR. BROOTS.     


540
00:42:32,983 --> 00:42:35,484
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?        


541
00:42:37,455 --> 00:42:42,358
        [ Clears Throat ]       
        TRACKING JAROD          
        IS A FULL-TIME JOB, SIR.


542
00:42:42,427 --> 00:42:47,028
<i>AND YOU'VE BEEN</i>                 
<i>PUTTING IN LONG HOURS.</i>          


543
00:42:47,097 --> 00:42:52,501
I'M DISTRESSED TO DISCOVER      
THAT YOU TOOK YOUR COMPUTER     
OFF THE NETWORK.                


544
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:55,471
[ Wheezing ]                    
IT MAKES ME WONDER...           


545
00:42:55,540 --> 00:42:58,074
IF YOUR LOYALTIES               
ARE TO THIS MISSION...          


546
00:42:58,142 --> 00:43:01,743
OR SOME PERSONAL ENDEAVOR.      


547
00:43:02,814 --> 00:43:05,380
        I-I DON'T HAVE          
        ANY PERSONAL ENDEAVORS. 


548
00:43:05,449 --> 00:43:07,382
PERHAPS                         
I SHOULD REACQUAINT YOU...      


549
00:43:07,452 --> 00:43:10,752
WITH THE CONSEQUENCES           
OF LYING TO THE CENTRE.         


550
00:43:10,821 --> 00:43:12,754
<i>[ Wheezing ]</i>                    


551
00:43:12,824 --> 00:43:15,791
        <i> BROOTS'S ACTIONS</i>       
        <i> ARE UNDER MY AUTHORITY.</i>


552
00:43:18,796 --> 00:43:23,432
THEN I SHOULD                   
HOLD YOU RESPONSIBLE            
FOR THE LACK OF RESULTS.        


553
00:43:25,870 --> 00:43:28,670
        YOU CAN DO              
        WHATEVER YOU LIKE,      


554
00:43:28,739 --> 00:43:32,774
    BUT WE WON'T GET ANY RESULTS
    UNTIL YOU GET OUT OF MY WAY.


555
00:43:38,116 --> 00:43:42,084
I HAVE BUSINESS TO ATTEND TO.   


556
00:43:42,153 --> 00:43:45,988
WE'LL DISCUSS THIS FURTHER      
AT ANOTHER TIME.                


557
00:43:56,634 --> 00:43:58,934
YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME.      


558
00:44:20,991 --> 00:44:22,924
            JAROD HAS EXPRESSED 
            HIS INABILITY...    


559
00:44:22,994 --> 00:44:26,328
    TO COMPLETE THE SIMULATION  
    WITHOUT ANOTHER PRETENDER.  


560
00:44:26,397 --> 00:44:29,631
AS A RESULT,                    
I'VE CONVINCED A COLLEAGUE      
TO ESTABLISH NEW PARAMETERS...  


561
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:31,633
    FOR THE PRETENDER PROGRAM.  


562
00:44:32,769 --> 00:44:35,437
        JAROD. THERE'S SOMEONE  
        I WANT YOU TO MEET.     


563
00:44:44,649 --> 00:44:47,616
JAROD, THIS IS KYLE.            


564
00:44:47,685 --> 00:44:50,386
KYLE, JAROD.                    


565
00:44:52,890 --> 00:44:55,591
    HI.                         
                    HI.         


566
00:45:00,631 --> 00:45:02,698
WHERE DID THEY TAKE YOU, KYLE?  


567
00:45:07,538 --> 00:45:09,137
        [ Locking Case ]        


568
00:45:11,942 --> 00:45:13,909
        <i> [ Door Slides Shut ]</i>   


569
00:45:13,978 --> 00:45:16,612
HE BURIED 'EM, JAROD.           
YOU SHOULD'VE BEEN THERE.       


570
00:45:16,681 --> 00:45:19,448
        - [ Jarod ]             
          ALL RIGHT.            
        - GOOD LUCK TO YOU.     


571
00:45:19,516 --> 00:45:21,816
THANK YOU.                      


572
00:45:21,885 --> 00:45:25,720
        SO, YOU TWO             
        ARE FINALLY GONNA START 
        YOUR NEW LIFE TOGETHER. 


573
00:45:25,789 --> 00:45:30,025
THANK YOU, JAROD.               
        SO, WHO ARE WE GONNA BE?


574
00:45:30,094 --> 00:45:33,228
        DON'T WORRY. NOBODY'S   
        EVER GONNA FIND YOU.    


575
00:45:33,297 --> 00:45:35,230
        I HAVE EXPERIENCE       
        WITH THIS SORT OF THING.


576
00:45:35,299 --> 00:45:37,232
        YOU'RE THE MARSHAL.     


577
00:45:37,301 --> 00:45:39,868
            WELL, NOT REALLY.   


578
00:45:39,937 --> 00:45:43,038
        ACTUALLY, TODAY,        
        I THINK I'LL BE A CHEF. 
[ Engine Starts ]               


579
00:45:47,778 --> 00:45:50,279
        [ Screaming, Cheering ] 


580
00:45:53,483 --> 00:45:55,617
                [ Chattering ]  


581
00:45:55,686 --> 00:45:58,053
        <i> [ Woman ]</i>              
        <i> HEY, COWBOY. WHAT'S</i>    
        <i> YOUR SECRET INGREDIENT?</i>


582
00:45:58,122 --> 00:46:01,589
WELL, NOW, IF I TOLD YOU THAT,  
IT WOULDN'T BE NO SECRET.       


583
00:46:04,862 --> 00:46:07,529
    HERE YOU GO, LITTLE LADY.   
    ENJOY.                      


584
00:46:40,264 --> 00:46:41,296
            [ Mews ]            


